*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Pietro Rizzuto]], Canadian politician (b. 1934)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Alfred Schnittke]], Russian composer (b. 1934)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Byron Farwell]], American historian (b. 1921)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Hewett]], English actor (b. 1922)
*  2002   &amp;ndash; [[Carmen Silvera]], English actress (b. 1922)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Roger Voudouris]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (b. 1954)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Henri Cartier-Bresson]], French photographer (b. 1908)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Bob Murphy (announcer)|Bob Murphy]], American sportscaster (b. 1924)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Françoise d'Eaubonne]], French activist (b. 1920)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Arthur Lee (musician)|Arthur Lee]], American singer-songwriter, musician, and producer ([[Love (band)|Love]]) (b. 1945)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Elisabeth Schwarzkopf]], German-English soprano (b. 1915)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[John Gardner (British writer)|John Gardner]], English author (b. 1926)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Skip Caray]], American sportscaster (b. 1939)
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Erik Darling]], American singer-songwriter ([[The Tarriers]] and [[The Rooftop Singers]]) (b. 1933)
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn]], Russian writer (b. 1918)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikolaos Makarezos]], Greek army officer (b. 1919)
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[Bubba Smith]], American football player and actor (b. 1945)
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; [[John Berry (speedway promoter)|John Berry]], English motorcycle racing promoter and manager (b. 1944)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Martin Fleischmann]], Czech-English chemist (b. 1927)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Paul McCracken]], American economist (b. 1915)
